  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling funds from their employer. However, taking into account the lack of a prior criminal record and the effort made toward partial restitution, a lengthy prison sentence is not warranted. A moderate period of incarceration is necessary to serve as a deterrent and punishment for the breach of fiduciary duty, after which the defendant can continue to pay back the remaining stolen funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
